
Task 3 — Company and Multiple Departments Injection.
Demonstrate setter-based dependency injection using a List collection in Spring 5, configured through Java-based configuration (AppConfig class) instead of XML.

🧱 Class-wise Design
1️.Department Class

Attributes:

String deptName

int deptId

Methods:

Setter methods for both fields.

A method showDepartment() to display department details.

2️.Company Class

Attributes:

List<Department> departments

Methods:

Setter method to inject the list of departments.

showDepartments() method to iterate and print department information.

3️. AppConfig Class (Java-based Configuration)

Responsibilities:

Annotated with @Configuration.

Define multiple Department beans (dept1, dept2, dept3) with unique data.

Define one Company bean.

Inject the list of department beans into the Company bean using Arrays.asList() inside the @Bean method.

4️. Main Class

Responsibilities:

Create an ApplicationContext using AnnotationConfigApplicationContext.

Load the AppConfig class.

Retrieve the Company bean from the context.

Invoke showDepartments() to display all department details.

📘 Expected Output
---- Company Departments ----
Department ID: 101, Name: IT
Department ID: 102, Name: HR
Department ID: 103, Name: Finance
